title: Tech had a rocky 2018. Here's what 2019 might look like.
text: CNBC's Josh Lipton reports on what hurt the tech sector in 2018, and what it might face in 2019.

title: Android apps sharing data with Facebook without users' consent: Report
text: Hotspot Shield security analyst Robert Siciliano on a cyber attack that hit major newspapers and a report that some popular Android apps send data to Facebook without consent.

title: The major IPOs expected in 2019
text: Constellation Research founder Ray Wang on the outlook for the IPO market and the boost to Netflix from 'Bird Box.'

title: Facebook might need to undergo 'fundamental change' in order to combat hate speech, says NYT's Ed Le
text: The New York Times' Ed Lee discusses the paper's story on Facebook moderators relying on incorrect info to police the social media site for hate speech and fake news.

title: Facebook vows to police its users, but how?
text: SocialFlow CEO Jim Anderson on Facebook vowing to police its users and LinkedIn co-founder Reid Hoffman apologizing for unknowingly funding a misinformation campaign in the 2017 Alabama Senate race.

title: Facebook under fire over secret rulebook
text: District Media Group President Beverly Hallberg and Dobson Policy Center Director Jenna Ellis discuss the report about Facebook's secret rulebook and the privacy concerns surrounding the social media giant.

title: Time for investors to buy into tech?
text: Constellation Research founder Ray Wang on the state of the tech sector.

title: Facebook now considered the least-trusted tech company: Survey
text: Transpire Ventures General Partner John Meyer on consumers' lack of trust in Facebook and the big tech trends to look forward too.

title: More room for tech stocks to drop?
text: BubbaTrading.com's Todd Horwitz and Kadina Group President Gary B. Smith on the outlook for stocks.

title: Ives: Tech sector is as negative as I've seen going back several years
text: Dan Ives of Wedbush Securities discusses the negative sentiment hanging over the tech sector, and which stocks could be good buying opportunities for investors in 2019.

title: Have to look at lack of anti-trust enforcement on social media giants, says Walter Isaacson
text: Walter Isaacson, Perella Weinberg Advisory partner and former chairman of CNN, and Recode EIC Kara Swisher, discuss the volatile year in tech, in the markets and the workplace.

title: Growth rates are slowing for tech sector, says Gene Munster
text: Brian Wieser, senior research analyst at Pivotal Research Group, and Gene Munster, managing partner at Loup Ventures, speak with  "Squawk Alley" on the slowing tech sector.

title: Facebook tried to explain how Netflix, Spotify were given access to user data
text: The Hill Media reporter Joe Concha on the privacy concerns surrounding Facebook.

title: Facebook users misinformed about how their data would be used?
text: Aspect Ventures co-founder Jennifer Fonstad on mounting concerns over user privacy on Facebook and the outlook for the IPO market.

title: Henry Blodget: We are in a bear market
text: Henry Blodget, Business Insider editor-in-chief, and Tom Forte, D.A. Davidson & Co. consumer internet analyst, speak to CNBC's "Squawk Alley" about the tech sector sell-off.

title: Facebook gave big tech firms access to users' private information | Squawk Box Europe
text: CNBC's Elizabeth Schulze discusses the fallout from Facebook's latest scandal.

title: Greycroft co-founder on Facebook, Google, Amazon monopoly concerns
text: Greycroft co-founder Alan Patricof on a recent surge in the entrepreneurial spirit, the state of the IPO market and antitrust concerns over tech companies such as Facebook, Google and Amazon.

title: Why Facebook Is Collecting So Much Personal Data
text: Rich Greenfield, a BTIG analyst, and Bloomberg's Sarah Frier discuss the report from the New York Times that Facebook Inc. had allowed more than 150 companies to access more personal data from users than it had disclosed. They speak with Bloomberg's Emily Chang on "Bloomberg Technology."

title: Kara Swisher: Some of Facebook's problems include sloppy management
text: Kara Swisher, Recode co-founder and editor-at-large, speaks to CNBC's "Squawk Alley" about the privacy concerns at Facebook.

title: Facebook's costs mount as data scandals deepen
text: CNBC's Julia Boorstin reports on Facebook's financial exposure from the fallout of several high-profile data scandals.

title: Facebook gave Netflix, Spotify access to users' messages according to reports
text: A  New York Times report alleges Facebook gave access to user messages to Netflix and Spotify. Microsoft and Amazon were also reportedly given access to data on users' friends.  Fox News senior judicial analyst Judge Andrew Napolitano weighs in.

title: Facebook shared user data with tech partners, NYT reports
text: Nick Confessore, New York Times investigative reporter, joins 'Squawk Box' to discuss his latest report on Facebook's user privacy practices.

title: Facebook under fire after NYT report company granted tech cos. access to user data
text: CNBC's Julia Boorstin reports on The New York Times' article on Facebook's misuse of user data and how it granted tech companies special access without the consent of its users.

title: DC Attorney General sues Facebook over role in Cambridge Analytica
text: CNBC's Julia Boorstin reports on the office of the Washington D.C. Attorney General suing Facebook for its role in the Cambridge Analytica scandal.

title: Can Facebook win back the trust of its users?
text: Tech expert Lance Ulanoff discusses the privacy concerns surrounding Facebook.

title: Global perception of meltdown in iPhone demand, says analyst
text: Michael Olson of Piper Jaffray discusses the firm's price target slash on Apple's stock with CNBC's "Power Lunch" team.

title: Amazon is the top pick of FANG stocks, says Baird strategist
text: John Blackledge, Cowen and Co. senior internet analyst, and Colin Sebastian, Robert W. Baird senior analyst, discuss which F.A.N.G stocks will hold up in 2019.

title: Prepping for 2019 Isn't Just Mitigating Risk -- How to Pick the Best Stocks
text: Watch full interview with JJ Kinahan, chief market strategist at TD Ameritrade.

title: Where traders are betting Facebook goes next. Plus, a trade update on Home Depot
text: "Halftime Report" trader Pete Najarian spots unusual options activity in shares of Facebook and Home Depot.

title: Time to buy tech? 4 trades
text: The "Fast Money" traders give you 4 busy in tech after a major reversal in the market today.

title: FANG stocks dip even as jobs remain steady
text: Mark May, senior internet analyst at Citi, and Mark Mahaney talk tech job numbers with CNBC's "Squawk Alley."

title: Democrats to take aim at Facebook, Google, Amazon and Apple: Charlie Gasparino
text: FBN's Charlie Gasparino reports that Democrats may soon take aim at Facebook, Google, Amazon and Apple.

title: You cannot be a bull on Netflix: Analyst
text: CNBC's "Power Lunch" team talks with Laura Martin, a senior analyst at Needham, on FANG stocks' drop.

title: Internal Facebook Emails Released: What They Reveal
text: A look at documents released by a U.K. lawmaker as part of a British parliamentary committee inquiry into “disinformation and fake news,” reveals how Facebook and CEO Mark Zuckerberg gave select developers special access to user data and deliberated on whether to sell that data.

title: Facebook board: Sandberg's request to probe Soros 'entirely appropriate'
text: CNBC's "Fast Money" team and Julia Boorstin discuss Facebook's board backing COO Sheryl Sandberg's request to have billionaire philanthropist George Soros investigated.

title: Amazon the number one tech pick for your portfolio?
text: Constellation Research principal analyst Ray Wang on the tech sector.

title: Sheryl Sandberg's philosophy is unrealistic in many ways: Carly Fiorina
text: Former Republican presidential candidate Carly Fiorina on former First Lady Michelle Obama's comments on Facebook COO Sheryl Sandberg's 'lean in' strategy.
